The paper deals with the problem of computing the cubicity of graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The focus is on trees, which are a fundamental data structure in computer science (cs.DS) and the algorithmic techniques used are randomized and deterministic polynomial time algorithms, which are topics in complexity theory (cs.CC) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
